Okamoto et al. (2010) studied the rise of a twisted column of cool plasma, which led to the formation of a prominence and a coronal cavity. The structure was seen at the limb, in Ca ii H (Hinode/SOT), in EUV (STEREO/EUVI), and the soft X-rays (Hinode/XRT). In the SDO-era, Li et al. (2012) combined EUV imaging with ground based Hα\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
