Vortex motions may be cardinal for the transfer of energy from the subsurface to the outer atmospheric layers of the Sun. Vortex-related MHD waves are considered a potential mechanism for this energy transport and the heating of the solar atmosphere with the estimated vertical Poynting flux providing a measure of electromagnetic energy flux streaming through it. Simulations by Shelyag et al. (2011a) suggested that vortex flows are the main source for a vertical Poynting flux sufficiently high to supply the necessary energy flux for the upper layers of the solar atmosphere. Wedemeyer-Böhm et al. (2012) estimated from simulations a net Poynting flux of 440Wm−2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
