				\begin{document}$( \boldsymbol{j} [\boldsymbol{E} + \boldsymbol{v} \times \boldsymbol{B}] ) \approx \eta _{A}\boldsymbol{j_{\perp}}^{2}$\end{document} (the contribution of the battery term can be safely neglected). The ambipolar diffusion allows to dissipate magnetic energy and convert it into thermal energy by dissipating currents that flow perpendicular to the magnetic field. At the same time, this dissipative effect will cause the removal of some fraction of the ideal Poynting flux, SEMideal\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
